@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";
}
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-12">
        <h1 class="display-4">ClubRight Screening Assessment</h1>
        <p>You have 90 minutes for this assessment. Please say how long and how you found it in "How did you find this assessment?".  (optional: this is your opportunity to show some flair!)</p>
    </div>

    <div class="col-4 text-start pe-5">
        <ol>
            <li class="mb-3">
                While debugging, any changes to the razor page will need to the whole application to be re-built/re-run for changes to take effect. Change the project file so that you can make UI changes without restarting.
            </li>
            <li class="mb-3">
                Create a button on the page that increments a digit on the page (this should be a server side call, not Javascript (apart from any inbuilt ajax functions))
            </li>
            <li class="mb-3">
                Create a second page which can be accessed from the nav menu, the contents of the page should be a header that says "Number of clicks" with a paragraph that says "The button was pressed X times" (replacing X for how many times the button was pressed in question 2)
            </li>
            <li class="mb-3">
                Create a button that takes a string as an input
                <ul>
                    <li>Reverse this string and output it on the page (eg "The quick brown fox" will output as "xof nworb kciuq ehT")</li>
                    <li>Reverse the words from the input string and output it on to the page (eg "The quick brown fox" will output as "fox brown quick The")</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="col">
        <div class="mb-5">
            <h3>Add your solution to question 2 here</h3>

            <p><button>Increment number by 1</button></p>
            <p><span>1</span></p>
            <hr />
        </div>

        <div class="mb-5">
            <h3>Add your solution to question 3 here</h3>
            <hr />
        </div>

        <form id="fsStringReverse">
            Input String to Reverse: <input type="text" id="reverseFunction" /><br />
            <input type="submit" value="Reverse String" />
        </form>
        <script>
            function reverseFunction() {
                var sample = document.getElementById('reverseFunction').value;
                var reversedOutput = '';

                for (var i = sample.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
                    reversedOutput += sample[i];
                }

                document.getElementById('reverseFunction').disabled = true;
                document.getElementById('reverseFunction').value = reversedOutput;
            }

            function submit(event) {
                event.preventDefault();
                reverseFunction();
            }

            document.getElementById('fsStringReverse').addEventListener('submit', submit);
        </script>


        <form id="fsStringWordsReverse">
            Input String to Reverse By Words: <input type="text" id="reverseByWords" /><br />
            <input type="submit" value="Reverse By Words" />
        </form>
        <script>

            function reverseByWords() {
                var sample = document.getElementById('reverseByWords').value;

                reversedOutput =  sample.split(' ')
                          .reverse()
                          .join(' ');

                document.getElementById('reverseByWords').disabled = true;
                document.getElementById('reverseByWords').value = reversedOutput;
            }

            function submit(event) {
                event.preventDefault();
                reverseByWords();
            }

            document.getElementById('fsStringWordsReverse').addEventListener('submit', submit);
        </script>

        <div class="mb-5">
            <h4>How did you find this assessment?</h4>
            <p>
                The assessment was really interesting.
                However I got stuck trying to solve the question 2, subsequently the 3 as well.
                I got a solution ant the end.
                Regarding the first question, I have thicked the HotReload button, and that
                keep the updates without restarting.
            </p>
        </div>

        <form method="post" asp-action="CounterInc">
            <button type="submit">Increment by 1</button>
        </form>
        <p>Count: <span>@ViewData["Increment"]</span></p>

    </div>
</div>
